WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.066 --> 00:00:02.950
Rune shapes, inscriptions - I've dedicated my

00:00:02.950 --> 00:00:05.800
life to studying these. The more I

00:00:05.800 --> 00:00:08.350
studied, the more I

00:00:08.350 --> 00:00:11.350
found the same shapes in the stars of the sky.

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:15.350
That's when I


00:00:15.916 --> 00:00:17.233
decided to dedicate myself to becoming a Rune Seeker. As

00:00:18.550 --> 00:00:23.150
Farrow kindly explained,
runes are very powerful ancient inscriptions. By

00:00:23.150 --> 00:00:26.350
socketing them into items, they
grant you even more power.

00:00:26.900 --> 00:00:30.300
During the League, by inscribing symbols onto remnants, you'll be able to choose

00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:33.983
from several types of crafting runes to enhance your items.


00:00:34.633 --> 00:00:38.183
When you encounter a remnant, it will


00:00:38.733 --> 00:00:39.866
have between two and seven empty slots. The

00:00:39.866 --> 00:00:42.783
more slots it has, the
more powerful the remnant encounter will be,

00:00:42.783 --> 00:00:45.450
but it will also give you more options.

00:00:45.450 --> 00:00:47.333
Early in the game, you'll

00:00:47.333 --> 00:00:49.400
choose simple damage runes or resistance runes.

00:00:49.750 --> 00:00:51.116
These

00:00:51.116 --> 00:00:52.616
can be obtained at lower levels than they normally are and

00:00:52.700 --> 00:00:54.433
give you a significant power boost. But this is where it gets really

00:00:54.650 --> 00:00:56.516
interesting. There

00:00:57.250 --> 00:01:00.233
are 22 runes that add or modify rune words.

00:01:00.483 --> 00:01:02.450
Rune words are a new resource that protects your character from death. You

00:01:03.033 --> 00:01:06.900
can use these runes to add an extra layer of defense, or you can

00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:10.150
use Kargul's rune skill to turn rune
words into offensive tools.  There are also

00:01:13.183 --> 00:01:16.600
13 runes that enhance specific weapon types.

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:19.833
For example, this one gives grenades a chance to explode again.

00:01:21.283 --> 00:01:24.566
Or, this one grants a new buff called Druid's Proficiency when you inflict a heavy stun on an enemy.

00:01:24.616 --> 00:01:26.200
 


00:01:28.950 --> 00:01:29.850
Furthermore, there are 22 runes

00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:32.850
designed to empower players at lower levels.


00:01:32.850 --> 00:01:35.850
For example, this one grants a large amount of elemental resistance.

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:38.683
This one grants a lot of spirit.

00:01:38.683 --> 00:01:42.300
These runes are powerful, but they are
designed to decrease in value as you level up. They will be useful

00:01:42.300 --> 00:01:45.300
when power leveling another character in the League. We have also


00:01:45.733 --> 00:01:47.933


00:01:47.933 --> 00:01:51.016
added 6 runes that expand your mod pool when you are doing high-level crafting.

00:01:51.600 --> 00:01:55.133
For example, socketing Katla's Gloom into gloves will allow you to

00:01:55.133 --> 00:01:58.516
craft a lot of new Decay mods. They

00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:00.650
can be used in damage over time builds.

00:02:01.216 --> 00:02:03.316
After socketing this type of rune, you can

00:02:03.316 --> 00:02:06.416
use regular Noble Orbs or Chaos Orbs to
try crafting new mods. There are also

00:02:08.666 --> 00:02:10.583
several runes that have powerful results for items, but they will

00:02:10.583 --> 00:02:13.900
permanently occupy a socket.

00:02:14.066 --> 00:02:17.183
For example, this one allows items to have an additional suffix.


00:02:21.200 --> 00:02:23.516
This one allows you to have a jewel socket.

00:02:29.166 --> 00:02:30.400
This type of rune

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:33.566
Elemental mods convert one element into another. They can upgrade

00:02:34.933 --> 00:02:37.700
other runes, some even going

00:02:37.700 --> 00:02:39.750
beyond their normal limits. The

00:02:42.133 --> 00:02:45.133
last one I'll show you is
Alder's Legacy. It's a special rune that, when

00:02:45.433 --> 00:02:50.266
socketed into a Kargul or Ezomite unique, destroys it and

00:02:50.266 --> 00:02:53.233
creates a rune with some of that unique's properties.


00:02:53.816 --> 00:02:54.983
For example, you can

00:02:54.983 --> 00:02:58.350
use it on Trampletoe to
create a Trampletoe Legacy rune.

00:02:58.500 --> 00:02:59.950
Socketing this into boots will make it deal 10%

00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:01.683


00:03:01.683 --> 00:03:05.233
overkill damage to all enemies within a 2m radius, just like the unique it was based on.


00:03:05.983 --> 00:03:08.700
What about Twisted Empyrean's Legacy?  You can

00:03:08.700 --> 00:03:10.466
shatter the twisted sky and add frost damage

00:03:10.466 --> 00:03:13.666
to all weapons based on your maximum mana. The


00:03:14.783 --> 00:03:17.900
Legacy of Aldur allows you to generate hundreds of runes with a
vast variety of unique effects. As I've

00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:19.950


00:03:22.516 --> 00:03:25.116
explained, you're probably
thinking that the number of runes is enormous. And you'd be

00:03:25.116 --> 00:03:26.350
right, because

00:03:26.350 --> 00:03:28.350
this is Runes of Aldur after all. But we didn't want to

00:03:28.350 --> 00:03:31.000
leave any old runes behind either. A

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:32.700
 
large portion of the ancient runes that haven't been used will

00:03:32.700 --> 00:03:34.800
receive buffs, which will

00:03:34.800 --> 00:03:37.233
greatly improve the crafting system. Experience the full potential of runes in the

00:03:37.566 --> 00:03:39.183
Return of the Ancients update on May 30th JST. See you then

00:03:39.183 --> 00:03:42.883
 
!

